&lt;p&gt;Much under-rated, the Wood Pigeon is increasingly in demand as an eating bird. Available as a whole bird or as breasts, they are simple to cook, available all year round and great value for money.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cooking tips:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pigeon should be cooked until pink, not fully brown. The meat has a delightful flavour, somewhere between beef and really good liver. Cook whole birds like a Grouse, otherwise pan fry seasoned breasts in butter for 90 seconds a side, then deglaze with sherry or balsamic vinegar, and rest for 3 minutes before carving. Try them in a warm salad with bacon and fried black pudding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The most in demand of all the wild ducks and famously hard to shoot, this is the smallest and best eating of the lot. We quite often get Teal in good numbers later in the season.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cooking tips:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Teal should be cooked like a Snipe. Poach in chicken stock for 4 minutes at 80&amp;deg;C (just below a simmer), then pat dry and colour in a pan with foaming butter and seasoning. Roast at 160&amp;deg;C for 4 minutes, then rest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Teal is truly a bird fit for a king. Eat two for dinner, using nothing but a large napkin, and your hands!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;A simply awesome cut of any deer, generally much bigger than a rack of lamb, and without the thick covering of fat. The bones are cut quite long for better presentation. This whole rack feeds four to six people comfortably.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;Cooking tips:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;This top quality cut comes tied ready to roast and carve. Cook pink as you would a wonderful piece of beef or lamb. Alternatively, cut between the bones to produce individual chops &amp;ndash; great on a barbecue.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

